rpg - random palette generator
------------------------------

generate random palettes for your terminal's colors

the palettes are random with the excpetion that min and max rgb values are
used to achieve somewhat sane colors


screenshots: https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36552788/94266156-02e57680-ff3a-11ea-8acc-6899816fc24e.png
             https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36552788/94266242-26a8bc80-ff3a-11ea-8e7c-1f917ccc8a07.png


dependencies
------------

* POSIX shell + mkdir, printf, pgrep and shuf
* hsetroot (optional)
    * used to set wallpaper color if picom or compton is running
* xsetroot (optional)
    * used to set wallpaper color otherwise


install
-------

clone rpg

    $ git clone https://github.com/fehawen/rpg.git

change working directory to rpg

    $ cd rpg

install rpg by running make install ***

    $ make install

add ~/.bin to the PATH export in your shellrc if not already present

    export PATH=~/bin:$PATH

persist colors by adding the following to your shellrc

    rpg reload

*** installs to ~/bin by default, and make install should thus not run as root


uninstall
---------

uninstall rpg by running make uninstall

    $ make uninstall


usage
-----

rpg d, rpg dark    - generate dark palette
rpg l, rpg light   - generate light palette
rpg r, rpg reload  - reload current palette
rpg c, rpg current - print current palette
